I haven't done a VW but you can do the whole system if you take it one wire 
at a time.

We've done several fully loaded hot rods.

Just takes time.

I'd use the same wiring layout as the VW though.


>Has anybody ever rewired their bus completely?  I am beginning to think 
>that the stock wiring layout is not so good.  Twice I have had smoke 
>coming from the wires.  Today after finally getting a rebuilt engine 
>running something went wrong with the starter and the wires under the dash 
>started smoking.  Now everything is wasted.   I am thinking about tearing 
>all the wires out and redoing it all in a more repair-friendly 
>fashion.  It looks to me like the main hot wire leading from the rear up 
>to the dash is about 1/2 the size it should be.  Also it appears that 
>there were no fusible links or anything on the wires.  Is there any reason 
>why a guy couldn't just run the wires along the floor inside the cabin or 
>along the ceiling in a pipe?  I notice the the wires are exposed at some 
>points underneath, that can't be good.  I have the bus from Hell.  GW

